SETaP coursework
# Campus Connect

A mobile and web application for students to share pinpoints of information and warnings on a campus map.

## Project Structure
```
uop_setap_cw/
├── frontend/          # Flutter app (mobile + web)
├── backend/           # FastAPI backend
├── docs/              # Project documentation
├── .gitignore
└── README.md
```

## Prerequisites

Before you start, make sure you have the following installed:

- **Flutter SDK** (3.0 or higher) - [Install Flutter](https://docs.flutter.dev/get-started/install)
- **Python** (3.9 or higher) - [Install Python](https://www.python.org/downloads/)
- **Git** - [Install Git](https://git-scm.com/downloads)

### Verify Installation
```bash
flutter --version
python3 --version
git --version
```

## Getting Started

### 1. Clone the Repository
```bash
git clone <repository-url>
cd uop_setap_cw
```

### 2. Frontend Setup (Flutter)
```bash
cd frontend
flutter pub get
flutter run  # For mobile
# OR
flutter run -d chrome  # For web
```

### 3. Backend Setup (FastAPI)
```bash
cd backend

# Create virtual environment
python3 -m venv venv

# Activate virtual environment
# On macOS/Linux:
source venv/bin/activate
# On Windows:
# venv\Scripts\activate

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Copy environment template
cp .env.example .env

# Run the server
uvicorn app.main:app --reload
```

The API will be available at `http://localhost:8000`

## Development Workflow

### Creating a New Branch
```bash
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name
```

### Making Changes

1. Make your changes in your branch
2. Test your code
3. Commit your changes:
```bash
   git add .
   git commit -m "Description of your changes"
```

### Submitting a Pull Request

1. Push your branch to GitHub:
```bash
   git push origin feature/your-feature-name
```
2. Go to the GitHub repository
3. Click "Pull requests" → "New pull request"
4. Select your branch and create the PR
5. Request review from team members
6. Wait for approval before merging

